%N A397868 Decimal expansion of the surface area of a canonical (dual-uniform) heptagonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397868 The heptagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the heptagonal antiprism.
%H A397868 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397868/b397868.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%H A397868 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HeptagonalTrapezohedron.html">Heptagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397868 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Heptagonal_antitegum">Heptagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397868 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397868 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_06">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 6</a>.
%F A397868 Equals (7/4)*csc(Pi/14)^2*sqrt(1 - 2*sin(3*Pi/14) + 4*cos(Pi/7)).
%F A397868 Equals the largest real root of x^6 - 4263*x^4 + 292922*x^2 + 1529437.
%e A397868 64.753796379583398014649210592998402858507498884391...
%t A397868 First[RealDigits[Root[#^6 - 4263*#^4 + 292922*#^2 + 1529437 &, 4], 10, 100]]
%t A397868 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397868 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 7}, "SurfaceArea"], 10, 100]]
%Y A397868 Cf. A397867 (volume), A397869 (inradius), A397870 (midradius), A397871 (height).
%Y A397868 Cf. A397872 (long edge).
%Y A397868 Cf. A397873 (small face angle), A397874 (large face angle), A397875 (dihedral angle).
%Y A397868 Cf. A394072 (surface area of the dual).
